    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Explore the global settings
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "Explore the different settings of the Exposure Override
          in the <b>Volume Global</b> GameObject. \r\n\r\n1) Delete your Global Volume
          in the <i>Hierarchy.</i> It isn\u2019t needed for the rest of the tutorials.\r\n\r\n2)
          In the <i>Hierarchy,</i> select the <b>Lighting</b> > <b>Volumes</b> >
          <b>Volume Global</b> GameObject.\r\n\r\n3) Look at the <i>Inspector</i>
          to see how the Global Volume exposure is set up.\r\n\r\n4) Select the other
          Volumes for each room, and study how each of them has specific <b>Limit
          Min</b> and <b>Limit Max</b> parameters.\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s very important
          to limit the automatic exposure in order to prevent it from over- or underexposing
          certain areas of the Scene. \r\n\r\nExperiment with different values for
          <b>Limit Min</b> and <b>Limit Max</b> to understand their impact on the
          perceived brightness of the image, especially when looking at very dark
          or very bright areas of the Scene.\r"
